(40, 1, '2014-01-08 14:45:30', '2014-01-08 14:45:30', 'Around 6:30 I woke up on January 1st 2014. After laying in bed for a few minutes I decided I''d go ahead and get up. Surprisingly enough I wasn''t feeling any after effects from the New Years party the night before. So after my shower I laid down and started thinking about 2014 and, well, normally. I don''t really buy into new years resolutions or anything that has any value to it "being a new year." Because the reality of it is, its just another day. My bank account didn''t care about the new years, my weight or job or anything of that matter didn''t care it was a new year. So making a resolution has always been sort of a waste to me, if you want to change something, why wait until its a new year? Just do it.\r\n\r\nSo back on track, I thinking about all that and earlier in the year of 2013 I had decided to start climbing more, being outside, getting back on my bike. MAYBE running? Why I don''t know, I hate running. But the other stuff has always been fun to me and I''ve been wanting to do that whole face your fears and get over being scared of heights sort of thing. And the 1st was my last day of vacation. I had had 2 weeks off from work and it was a pretty uneventful vacation really. So it just hit me, "get on your laptop, find a place to go, and go there."\r\n<div class="content-img"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-189" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/097c943c731511e393331229d9ee6ec7_8-300x300.jpg" alt="wichita mountains" width="300" height="300" /><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-192" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/a6c3d790731611e395c312f4a385c1a1_8-300x300.jpg" alt="wichita mountains" width="300" height="300" /></div>\r\nAnd around 7:30 I was loading up my car and hitting the road to go to Wichita Mountains in Oklahoma. About a 4 hour drive there. I was going to go climb Elk Mountain, which sits with a peak of ~2,400ft. And then drive up to Mount Scott afterwards for lunch on the edge. The thing about the Wichita Mountains is the climb isn''t very difficult, just a hike up. But the place offers some great places to do top rope and bouldering. So I made the climb, it was a fun one, did some bouldering. I immediately fell in love with the climbing experience and since then I''ve already got a membership at a local indoor climbing gym and I go every other day. Hopefully on my upcoming trip to TN I''ll find some good places to climb around there, we shall see.\r\n<div class="content-img">\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-194" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/ac64dd30732411e382b10e088dd9d980_8-300x300.jpg" alt="wichita mountains subaru" width="300" height="300" />\r\n</div>\r\nOverall, the trip was great. I''m glad I got up and just left. That''s one thing I think is the biggest stopping factor in me is just getting up and doing it. I''ll sit around and think about how awesome it is to do this and that but when it comes to getting up and doing it. I find an excuse not to do it. And that is my overall goal.\r\n\r\nHere''s to this weekend and cycling around lake Ray Roberts!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Welcome 2014', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'so-its-2014', '', '', '2014-01-27 17:17:54', '2014-01-27 17:17:54', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/?p=40', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(43, 1, '2014-01-08 14:45:30', '2014-01-08 14:45:30', 'and i thought it would be a cool idea to get off my ass and go climb a mountain(ish).\r\n\r\nunfortunately the bad thing about living in dallas is that you''re about 4 hours drive away from anything really worth a damn when it comes to outdoor activities. at least for me anyways. so it''s about a 10 hour drive to guadalupe peak, about 4 hours to hill country and im not really even sure whats out that way. but it''s also about 4 hours to wichita mountains. so i got up and took off to go see what was out there. and it was the best trip of the year, easily.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-41" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/097c943c731511e393331229d9ee6ec7_8.jpg" alt="climbing wichita mountains" width="640" height="640" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nso it took me about 2 hours to climb and do my exploring there. and after that i took off and drove up to mount scott, which is the tallest mountain in this area. and had my lunch out of the back of my car there.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-42" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/ac64dd30732411e382b10e088dd9d980_8.jpg" alt="subaru time go" width="640" height="640" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\noverall a nice experience and i really enjoyed being outside. it was a good start to the new years id say.', 'so its 2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-08 14:45:30', '2014-01-08 14:45:30', '', 40, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
