(138, 1, '2014-01-16 20:28:53', '2014-01-16 20:28:53', 'Around 6:30 I woke up on January 1st 2014. After laying in bed for a few minutes I decided I''d go ahead and get up. Surprisingly enough I wasn''t feeling any after effects from the New Years party the night before. So after my shower I laid down and started thinking about 2014 and, well, normally. I don''t really buy into new years resolutions or anything that has any value to it "being a new year." Because the reality of it is, its just another day. My bank account didn''t care about the new years, my weight or job or anything of that matter didn''t care it was a new year. So making a resolution has always been sort of a waste to me, if you want to change something, why wait until its a new year? Just do it.\n\nSo back on track, I thinking about all that and earlier in the year of 2013 I had decided to start climbing more, being outside, getting back on my bike. MAYBE running? Why I don''t know, I hate running. But the other stuff has always been fun to me and I''ve been wanting to do that whole face your fears and get over being scared of heights sort of thing. And the 1st was my last day of vacation. I had had 2 weeks off from work and it was a pretty uneventful vacation really. So it just hit me, "get on your laptop, find a place to go, and go there."\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAnd around 7:30 I was loading up my car and hitting the road to go to Wichita Mountains in Oklahoma. About a 4 hour drive there. I was going to go climb Elk Mountain, which sits with a peak of ~2,400ft. And then drive up to Mount Scott afterwards for lunch on the edge. The thing about the Wichita Mountains is the climb isn''t very difficult, just a hike up. But the place offers some great places to do top rope and bouldering. So I made the climb, it was a fun one, did some bouldering. I immediately fell in love with the climbing experience and since then I''ve already got a membership at a local indoor climbing gym and I go every other day. Hopefully on my upcoming trip to TN I''ll find some good places to climb around there, we shall see.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nOverall, the trip was great. I''m glad I got up and just left. That''s one thing I think is the biggest stopping factor in me is just getting up and doing it. I''ll sit around and think about how awesome it is to do this and that but when it comes to getting up and doing it. It''s jus\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-41" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/097c943c731511e393331229d9ee6ec7_8.jpg" alt="climbing wichita mountains" width="640" height="640" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-42" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/ac64dd30732411e382b10e088dd9d980_8.jpg" alt="subaru time go" width="640" height="640" />', 'Welcome 2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-01-16 20:28:53', '2014-01-16 20:28:53', '', 40, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/40-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2014-01-16 20:29:39', '2014-01-16 20:29:39', 'Around 6:30 I woke up on January 1st 2014. After laying in bed for a few minutes I decided I''d go ahead and get up. Surprisingly enough I wasn''t feeling any after effects from the New Years party the night before. So after my shower I laid down and started thinking about 2014 and, well, normally. I don''t really buy into new years resolutions or anything that has any value to it "being a new year." Because the reality of it is, its just another day. My bank account didn''t care about the new years, my weight or job or anything of that matter didn''t care it was a new year. So making a resolution has always been sort of a waste to me, if you want to change something, why wait until its a new year? Just do it.\r\n\r\nSo back on track, I thinking about all that and earlier in the year of 2013 I had decided to start climbing more, being outside, getting back on my bike. MAYBE running? Why I don''t know, I hate running. But the other stuff has always been fun to me and I''ve been wanting to do that whole face your fears and get over being scared of heights sort of thing. And the 1st was my last day of vacation. I had had 2 weeks off from work and it was a pretty uneventful vacation really. So it just hit me, "get on your laptop, find a place to go, and go there."\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd around 7:30 I was loading up my car and hitting the road to go to Wichita Mountains in Oklahoma. About a 4 hour drive there. I was going to go climb Elk Mountain, which sits with a peak of ~2,400ft. And then drive up to Mount Scott afterwards for lunch on the edge. The thing about the Wichita Mountains is the climb isn''t very difficult, just a hike up. But the place offers some great places to do top rope and bouldering. So I made the climb, it was a fun one, did some bouldering. I immediately fell in love with the climbing experience and since then I''ve already got a membership at a local indoor climbing gym and I go every other day. Hopefully on my upcoming trip to TN I''ll find some good places to climb around there, we shall see.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOverall, the trip was great. I''m glad I got up and just left. That''s one thing I think is the biggest stopping factor in me is just getting up and doing it. I''ll sit around and think about how awesome it is to do this and that but when it comes to getting up and doing it. I find an excuse not to do it. And that is my overall goal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHere''s to this weekend and cycling around lake Ray Roberts!\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-41" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/097c943c731511e393331229d9ee6ec7_8.jpg" alt="climbing wichita mountains" width="640" height="640" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-42" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/ac64dd30732411e382b10e088dd9d980_8.jpg" alt="subaru time go" width="640" height="640" />', 'Welcome 2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-16 20:29:39', '2014-01-16 20:29:39', '', 40, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
