(167, 1, '2014-01-22 16:38:40', '2014-01-22 16:38:40', 'So for about 3 weeks now I''ve been going to an indoor rock climbing gym with a good friend of mine. We signed up thinking it would be a fun way to get exercise in that we could enjoy and have fun with. Plus I can look at this as a bonus to helping me climbing when I go hiking and etc.\r\n<div class="content-img"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-188" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/63f44a7c7fd611e3a7dc1272c310b776_8-300x300.jpg" alt="summit rock climbing gym" width="300" height="300" /><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-186" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/04a76b9e7aef11e395760aa89e374bbe_8-300x300.jpg" alt="summit rock climbing gym" width="300" height="300" />\r\n</div>\r\nI''ve always been scared of heights, I mean of course most people are... But I''ve always been terrified really. I put it at my number 1. And this was a good way for me to sort of face that fear head on. And I''ll tell you the first couple climbs were a bit dicey, the further I got up the more and more I felt myself just start shaking from the height of it all. But we''ve been going every other day for 3 weeks now and I can say the biggest improvement I''ve noticed, is that now when I climb my mind isn''t racing with possibilities of falling. My mind is racing with thoughts to my next foothold or handhold. I''m no longer worried about falling or being high up, I''m trying to solve the puzzle of the route.\r\n\r\nWe''ve started getting into routines and trying out different training exercises like bouldering one day for strength and balance, then top rope the next day for endurance and speed. I''ve also found it''s quite fun to just climb for fun and not follow any routes but make up my own. Doing leap exercises and things like that are crazy amounts of fun. And I might add, today is a climbing day so I''ll be counting down the hours until I jet out from work!', 'Enter Summit Rock Climbing Gym', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'enter-summit-rock-climbing-gym', '', '', '2014-01-27 17:15:05', '2014-01-27 17:15:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/?p=167', 0, 'post', '', 0),
