(198, 1, '2014-01-24 18:51:18', '2014-01-24 18:51:18', 'I''ve been on a search for a dog lately. For the past 5 or 6 months actually... The idea came to me when I decided I wanted a companion alongside me with my travels. And I understand I can''t always plan accordingly with my friends and sometimes I prefer to do things my way which means doing things other friends may not want to be doing. A dog would be the perfect ride along companion for a lot of these trips. So I began looking for a dog that wasn''t too big, wasn''t too small. As I do live in a small apartment and he/she would have to be comfortable in that environment. But I also wanted a bigger dog just to make their traveling easier on them.So as of last Sunday January the 19th I was helping a friend and his wife move and she mentioned swinging by the shelter to see if they had any dogs that fit my needs. And as it happened one did, on all marks too! She was new to the shelter, while all the other dogs were carrying away barking non stop she was quiet as a mouse. Calm and reserved. So I got her out to play around and she seemed to do very well. She knew commands like sit and she seemed well behaved. So I pulled the trigger and took her home that very day.\r\n\r\nSince she didn''t have a name I went with Chiguhr, which, if you don''t know. Is the name of the bad guy in No Country for Old Men. Her name came to me when we were leaving and they had been calling her SugarBaker in the shelter, my friends wife said, "Oh you should name her Sugar!" and from there I decided, "hey! What about Chiguhr!?" And it stuck!\r\n\r\nSo without further ado let me introduce her here!\r\n<div class="content-img">\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-190" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/134cc11e815a11e3b76a12716b453d94_8-300x300.jpg" alt="chiguhr" width="300" height="300" /><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-187" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/6c4e9a0a816211e3a6dd0a3241c4ea3f_8-300x300.jpg" alt="chiguhr" width="300" height="300" />\r\n</div>\r\nShe''s a German Shepherd mix and she''s just the right size! You can tell she''s got a little Corgi in her face too, and I think that helps keep her relatively smaller than other GSD''s. She weighed in at 46lbs at the vet.\r\n\r\nOh the vet...\r\n\r\nSo I scheduled her vet visit when I noticed she had a bit of a limp, and I think that came from when we were playing frisbee indoors, yeah I know. So we went in yesterday, Thursday the 23rd. She got her an X-ray, strained her ACL apparently, and some pills to keep that under wraps. She also got her rabies and microchip and all that matter. But then the surprise hit us when she came back positive for heartworms. No bueno there at all. So it looks like I''ll be calling in an appointment to get that process started next week. Also means shes going to be keeping chill for a few months during this process so she won''t get to make that upcoming roadtrip in Feb unfortunately.\r\n\r\nBut it''ll be okay, she doesn''t seem to be showing any signs which is a good thing and she should make a speedy recovery! More on all that later. Until then, she''s probably at home hanging out in this same spot...\r\n\r\nPeace! Time to climb!', 'Welcome Chiguhr', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome-chiguhr', '', '', '2014-01-27 17:12:02', '2014-01-27 17:12:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/?p=198', 0, 'post', '', 0),
