maller than other GSD''s. She weighed in at 46lbs at the vet.\r\n\r\nOh the vet...\r\n\r\nSo I scheduled her vet visit when I noticed she had a bit of a limp, and I think that came from when we were playing frisbee indoors, yeah I know. So we went in yesterday, Thursday the 23rd. She got her an X-ray, strained her ACL apparently, and some pills to keep that under wraps. She also got her rabies and microchip and all that matter. But then the surprise hit us when she came back positive for heartworms. No bueno there at all. So it looks like I''ll be calling in an appointment to get that process started next week. Also means shes going to be keeping chill for a few months during this process so she won''t get to make that upcoming roadtrip in Feb unfortunately.\r\n\r\nBut it''ll be okay, she doesn''t seem to be showing any signs which is a good thing and she should make a speedy recovery! More on all that later. Until then, she''s probably at home hanging out in this same spot...\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-187" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/6c4e9a0a816211e3a6dd0a3241c4ea3f_8.jpg" alt="chiguhr" />\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPeace! Time to climb!', 'Welcome Chiguhr', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '198-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-24 22:06:46', '2014-01-24 22:06:46', '', 198, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/198-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(204, 1, '2014-01-24 22:08:41', '2014-01-24 22:08:41', 'So for about 3 weeks now I''ve been going to an indoor rock climbing gym with a good friend of mine. We signed up thinking it would be a fun way to get exercise in that we could enjoy and have fun with. Plus I can look at this as a bonus to helping me climbing when I go hiking and etc.\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-188" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/63f44a7c7fd611e3a7dc1272c310b776_8.jpg" alt="summit rock climbing gym" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nI''ve always been scared of heights, I mean of course most people are... But I''ve always been terrified really. I put it at my number 1. And this was a good way for me to sort of face that fear head on. And I''ll tell you the first couple climbs were a bit dicey, the further I got up the more and more I felt myself just start shaking from the height of it all. But we''ve been going every other day for 3 weeks now and I can say the biggest improvement I''ve noticed, is that now when I climb my mind isn''t racing with possibilities of falling. My mind is racing with thoughts to my next foothold or handhold. I''m no longer worried about falling or being high up, I''m trying to solve the puzzle of the route.\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-186" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/04a76b9e7aef11e395760aa89e374bbe_8.jpg" alt="summit rock climbing gym"/>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nWe''ve started getting into routines and trying out different training exercises like bouldering one day for strength and balance, then top rope the next day for endurance and speed. I''ve also found it''s quite fun to just climb for fun and not follow any routes but make up my own. Doing leap exercises and things like that are crazy amounts of fun. And I might add, today is a climbing day so I''ll be counting down the hours until I jet out from work!', 'Enter Summit Rock Climbing Gym', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '167-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-24 22:08:41', '2014-01-24 22:08:41', '', 167, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/167-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
