(207, 1, '2014-01-24 22:11:35', '2014-01-24 22:11:35', 'Around 6:30 I woke up on January 1st 2014. After laying in bed for a few minutes I decided I''d go ahead and get up. Surprisingly enough I wasn''t feeling any after effects from the New Years party the night before. So after my shower I laid down and started thinking about 2014 and, well, normally. I don''t really buy into new years resolutions or anything that has any value to it "being a new year." Because the reality of it is, its just another day. My bank account didn''t care about the new years, my weight or job or anything of that matter didn''t care it was a new year. So making a resolution has always been sort of a waste to me, if you want to change something, why wait until its a new year? Just do it.\r\n\r\nSo back on track, I thinking about all that and earlier in the year of 2013 I had decided to start climbing more, being outside, getting back on my bike. MAYBE running? Why I don''t know, I hate running. But the other stuff has always been fun to me and I''ve been wanting to do that whole face your fears and get over being scared of heights sort of thing. And the 1st was my last day of vacation. I had had 2 weeks off from work and it was a pretty uneventful vacation really. So it just hit me, "get on your laptop, find a place to go, and go there."\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-189" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/097c943c731511e393331229d9ee6ec7_8.jpg" alt="wichita mountains" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nAnd around 7:30 I was loading up my car and hitting the road to go to Wichita Mountains in Oklahoma. About a 4 hour drive there. I was going to go climb Elk Mountain, which sits with a peak of ~2,400ft. And then drive up to Mount Scott afterwards for lunch on the edge. The thing about the Wichita Mountains is the climb isn''t very difficult, just a hike up. But the place offers some great places to do top rope and bouldering. So I made the climb, it was a fun one, did some bouldering. I immediately fell in love with the climbing experience and since then I''ve already got a membership at a local indoor climbing gym and I go every other day. Hopefully on my upcoming trip to TN I''ll find some good places to climb around there, we shall see.\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-192" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/a6c3d790731611e395c312f4a385c1a1_8.jpg" alt="wichita mountains" />\r\n</div>\r\nOverall, the trip was great. I''m glad I got up and just left. That''s one thing I think is the biggest stopping factor in me is just getting up and doing it. I''ll sit around and think about how awesome it is to do this and that but when it comes to getting up and doing it. I find an excuse not to do it. And that is my overall goal.\r\n<div class="full-img">\r\n  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-194" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/ac64dd30732411e382b10e088dd9d980_8.jpg" alt="wichita mountains subaru"/>\r\n</div>\r\nHere''s to this weekend and cycling around lake Ray Roberts!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Welcome 2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-24 22:11:35', '2014-01-24 22:11:35', '', 40, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(208, 1, '2014-01-27 17:21:55', '2014-01-27 17:21:55', 'And of course she was great! Got her a little bit of backyard fun in before her heartworm treatments started today. So she''ll be spending the night at the vet and I''ll be able to go get her after work tomorrow. Hopefully she does well, apparently I have to keep her from excitement and exercise for like 2 months. Which may or may not be difficult. So far she''s been a pretty chill gal. But she also wants to go run around and play games, I can tell. And 2 months of chilling may be tough haha. Especially when I personally want to go running around and playing frisbee with her too.\r\n<div class="content-img">\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-226" src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/chiguhr-01-225x300.jpg" alt="chiguhr at my parents" width="225" height="300" />\r\n</div>\r\nWe''ll have to see.\r\n\r\nI also got rid of my bed in my process to become more minimalistic and I''ve bought the indoor hanging kit from ENO to hang up my hammock as my bed. Also works great as a lounging around watch tv read a book kind of place. I approve, highly! I had the best nights sleep in a long time, plus it just gives a whole different vibe to chilling and getting some rest in. Since it''s a step away from the traditional sleeping situation it feels like a different environment.\r\n<div class="content-img">\r\n<img src="http://localhost:8888/bunkk/media/9862685a86e011e38d3812c086046c3b_8-300x300.jpg" alt="me in my hammock" width="300" height="300" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-228" />\r\n</div>', 'Chiguhr met my parents.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chiguhr-met-my-parents', '', '', '2014-01-27 18:22:08', '2014-01-27 18:22:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/bunkk/?p=208', 0, 'post', '', 0),
